—and of poetry and literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEpic poetry, LatinxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aaeneid, vergil, virgil, rome, mythology, history, literature, prehistory, heroism, aeneas, aeneis, epic poetry, allegory, apollonius, homer, classicism, language, prosody, narrative, distancing, interiority, tragedy, empire, literary criticism, nonfiction, nachleben, fall, decline, dissolution, politics, hero, sacrifice, war, destruction, violence, gods, classics, ancient world, greece.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1960-1989z978311066784440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226252377423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226252377/original  a978-3-11-066784-4  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1960-1989c1960d1989  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles